INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (76,2,'2010-01-08 10:03:15','2010-01-08 14:03:15','<h3>How We Got Started</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://gacarrigan.wpengine.com/about/original-bag/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2182\"><img class=\"alignright\" alt=\"leather drawstring bag\" src=\"http://gacarrigan.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/original-bag-300x300.png\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" /></a>West Coast/East Bags got its start in 2012 when Gail Carrigan rediscovered an adorable handbag that her mother carried everywhere in the 1960s. She loved the bag, but let’s say it was a “little worn.” She decided to remake a bag for herself and then for her sisters. And there the design instinct kicked in. Why not create the bag in different materials, including leather, denim, brocade and wedding dress material?\r\n\r\nWhat has been just as important to Gail as developing the perfect essentials bag, is ensuring that every every bag is produced to the highest quality standards and that every customer is entirely satisfied with her bag.\r\n\r\nWest Coast/East sources all materials in the US, and attempts to reuse materials, including denim jeans, brocade upholstery samples, and bridal dresses.\r\n\r\nGail was born in New Jersey, moved west to the San Francisco Bay Area at a young age, and then returned east to the Boston Area in 2000. Design influences from the West Coast and East Coast – as well as an interest in artisan craft – come together in these bags.\r\n\r\nWest Coast / East, is an artisan handmade accessories business, specializing in distinctive accessories for eclectic and discerning women.\r\n\r\nWe are always happy to hear your comments and feedback. Please contact us at 781.728.9190 or at gacarrigan@westcoast-east.com.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><em>Many thanks for visiting our site!</em></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About us','','publish','open','closed','','about','','','2013-01-23 21:14:50','2013-01-24 01:14:50','',0,'http://localhost/test/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0);
