INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2225,2,'2013-01-22 16:34:32','2013-01-22 20:34:32','<span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">As we mentioned in the About Us page, we starting making these bags not long ago, basing the design on a 1960s purse found while cleaning out an estate. We developed a few prototypes and then asked for feedback from friend, relatives and anybody else we could get to weigh in.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">We got recommendations to add longer straps so the bag could be carried on a shoulder, add pockets to the bags, and make them larger. All great suggestions that we are taking to heart and may add in future bags.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">We\'ve also received suggestions to make the bags in bright colors, add rhinestones and other adornments, and dress them up. In other words, give the bags some \"bling.\" That\'s the question we are grappling with now. The original bag was designed to be rustic chic, like Minnetonka loafers and Native American beadwork. It\'s in that spirit that we designated the names of the the bags after places in America with Indian names.</span>\n\nDo we keep the bags rustic or design them with more punch? Now it\'s your turn to weigh in and give us feedback. What would you like to see in  newly designed bags?','To Bling or Not to Bling?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1-autosave','','','2013-01-22 16:34:32','2013-01-22 20:34:32','',1,'http://www.westcoast-east.com/1-autosave/',0,'revision','',0);
